<paragraph blockId="18.[807,1423,1353,1405]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis box="[807,926,1353,1374]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Apex of ovipositor strongly deflected ventrally and dorsoventrally flattened (
<figureCitation box="[1221,1349,1383,1405]" captionStart="Figures 48–55" captionStartId="19.[156,246,1072,1091]" captionTargetBox="[798,1166,721,890]" captionTargetId="figure-387@19.[796,1169,718,877]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figures 48–55. Melaloncha spp., ovipositors. Figs 48–50: dorsal. Figs 51–55: left lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5439629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5439629/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 53-55</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[807,1424,1429,1543]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis box="[807,993,1429,1451]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Included species</emphasis>
. This group includes 
<taxonomicName authority="Brown, 2004" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2004" box="[1269,1423,1429,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horologica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1269,1423,1429,1451]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">M. horologica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[807,897,1460,1481]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Brown, 2004" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2004" box="[913,1034,1460,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[913,1034,1460,1482]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">M. spatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1047,1135,1460,1481]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Brown, 2004" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2004" box="[1202,1323,1461,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vargasi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1202,1323,1461,1482]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">M. vargasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1335,1424,1460,1481]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The last two species are more closely related and form a separate group, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2004" box="[1061,1182,1521,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatula">
<emphasis box="[1061,1182,1521,1543]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">M. spatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-series (below).
</paragraph>
